  "texts": [
    "• A journal has a cross-field publishing practice with a narrow field if that field is amongst the Scopus narrow fields that the journal is 2nd to 5th most similar to (i.e., a top 5 similar field, but not the top field).",
    "The second category is separated out from the first and third, despite not being in the research questions, for journals with publishing practices that are neither clearly specialist nor clearly cross-field.",
    "• The remaining journals have an unrelated research publishing practice relative to a Scopus narrow field.",
    "Thus, each journal will be classified once in either of the first two categories, four times in the third category and the remaining 333-5 = 328 times in the last category.",
    "The choice of five fields for the cross-field definition is again relatively arbitrary here."
  ],
